cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI

This paper discusses privacy issues related to IoT devices and proposes a traffic analysis framework based on sequence-learning techniques like LSTM. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also deals with network traffic generated in the smart home network, which suggests it could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of neural networks for traffic analysis makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for privacy protection, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
